<p>Next, head to the <strong>Formidable ¬ª Add-Ons</strong> screen in your WordPress dashboard. Here, you need to find the &#8216;Visual Views&#8217; addon and switch the toggle to activate it.</p>



<p>This add-on is the key to displaying your donations in a beautiful fundraising thermometer. It takes the form data ‚Äî including each donation ‚Äî and shows it as a progress bar that updates automatically.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="307" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-visual-views-addon-in-formidable-forms.png" alt="Install the Visual Views addon in Formidable Forms" class="wp-image-370236" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-visual-views-addon-in-formidable-forms.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-visual-views-addon-in-formidable-forms-300x135.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>With Visual Views, you can fully customize how your thermometer looks and where it appears on your site, giving you both functionality and flexibility for your fundraiser.</p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-add-and-configure-a-payment-gateway">Step 2: Add and Configure a Payment Gateway</h5>



<p>Since you‚Äôre already in the <strong>Add-Ons</strong> section, I also recommend installing your preferred payment add-on.</p>



<p>This step is important because I&#8217;m going to show you how to create a donation form that comes with a built-in payment field. Connecting a payment gateway ensures that people can actually donate through the form. </p>



<p>Formidable Forms supports popular options like <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/opinion/stripe-vs-paypal-wordpress/" title="Stripe vs. PayPal: Which Is Better for Your WordPress Site?">Stripe and PayPal</a>, so you can choose what works best for your nonprofit or fundraiser.</p>



<p>For most users, Stripe is the easiest choice. It handles multiple payment types, like credit and debit cards, Apple Pay, and Google Pay, and keeps donations secure.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="346" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-stripe-addon-in-formidable-forms.png" alt="Install the Stripe addon in Formidable Forms" class="wp-image-370238" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-stripe-addon-in-formidable-forms.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/install-stripe-addon-in-formidable-forms-300x153.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>After activating the add-on, navigate to the <strong>Formidable ¬ª Global Settings <strong>¬ª</strong> Payments</strong> page from the dashboard and click the &#8216;Connect to Stripe&#8217; button.</p>



<p>You can now link your account to Formidable Forms.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="327" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/click-connect-to-stripe-button-in-formidable-forms.png" alt="Click the Connect to Stripe button in Formidable Forms" class="wp-image-370239" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/click-connect-to-stripe-button-in-formidable-forms.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/click-connect-to-stripe-button-in-formidable-forms-300x144.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once completed, you‚Äôll be redirected back to WordPress, and a green checkmark will confirm that your Stripe account is connected successfully. </p>



<p>Now, donations collected through your charity template will update your fundraising thermometer automatically.  </p>



<h5 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-3">Step 3: Use the Charity Tracker Template</h5>



<p>Now, it‚Äôs time to install the Formidable Forms Charity Tracker Application Template. I‚Äôve tried this template with a few demo campaigns, and it really cuts down on setup time.</p>



