<p>The post <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/show-wordpress-org-reviews-in-wordpress/">How I Turned My WordPress.org Reviews Into Powerful Social Proof</a> first appeared on <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com">WPBeginner</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Nouman Yaqoob";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34913:"<p>While developing my own WordPress plugins, I realized that earning people&#8217;s trust was often harder than building the product itself. You can have great features and reliable support, but if someone hasn&#8217;t heard of you before, they will still hesitate to click ‚ÄúInstall‚Äù or ‚ÄúBuy.‚Äù</p>



<p>That‚Äôs why I recommend showing real WordPress.org reviews and ratings directly on your own website. Seeing authentic feedback from existing users can help new visitors feel confident about choosing your plugin or theme. </p>



<p>It‚Äôs a simple addition that can instantly boost credibility and conversions.</p>



<p>In this guide, I‚Äôll show you how to display live WordPress.org plugin and theme reviews on your site ‚Äî no coding required. </p>



