<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-2-create-a-new-review-feed">Step 2: Create a New Review Feed</h4>



<p>Now it&#8217;s time to set up your first review feed.</p>



<p>Navigate to <strong>Reviews Feed ¬ª All Feeds</strong> in your WordPress dashboard and click the &#8216;Add New&#8217; button. This will open the feed creation wizard, which will guide you through connecting to WordPress.org.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="296" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/reviewsfeedpro-creating-reviews-feed.png" alt="Creating a reviews feed on your WordPress website" class="wp-image-357941" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/reviewsfeedpro-creating-reviews-feed.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/reviewsfeedpro-creating-reviews-feed-300x131.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>From here, you can see that the plugin supports multiple review platforms, including <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-show-google-facebook-and-yelp-reviews-in-wordpress/" title="How I Show Google, Facebook, and Yelp Reviews in WordPress">Google, Facebook, and Yelp</a>. But for this tutorial, I&#8217;m focusing specifically on WordPress.org plugin and theme reviews.</p>



<p>So, from the list of available review sources, let&#8217;s select &#8216;WordPress.org&#8217; and click &#8216;Next&#8217;.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="434" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg.png" alt="Choosing WordPress.org as the review source" class="wp-image-368757" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg-300x191.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>The setup wizard will now prepare to connect your feed to WordPress.org&#8217;s review system.</p>



<p>This connection allows the plugin to automatically pull in fresh reviews from any WordPress.org plugin or theme page that you specify.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-3-connect-your-wordpress-org-account">Step 3: Add Your WordPress.org Plugin or Theme as a Source</h4>



<p>To connect your review feed to specific WordPress.org reviews, you&#8217;ll need to provide <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/website-url-parts-explained-for-beginners/" title="What Is a Website URL (Important Parts Explained for Beginners)">the URL</a> of the plugin or theme with the reviews you want to display.</p>



<p>You can open a new browser tab and navigate to the WordPress.org page for your chosen plugin or theme.</p>



<p>Let&#8217;s say you want to show reviews for a <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/5-best-contact-form-plugins-for-wordpress-compared/" title="I Tried Best WordPress Contact Form Plugins &amp; Here Are My Top Picks">contact form plugin</a>.</p>



<p>Simply go to that plugin&#8217;s official WordPress.org page and copy the complete URL from your browser&#8217;s address bar.</p>



<p>For example, the correct URL for the WPForms plugin is¬†<code>https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpforms-lite/</code>. </p>



<p>Make sure you copy the link from the main page, not from the reviews or support tabs.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="378" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/wordpressorg-wpforms-plugin-url.png" alt="Copying a plugin's WordPress.org URL" class="wp-image-368759" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/wordpressorg-wpforms-plugin-url.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/wordpressorg-wpforms-plugin-url-300x167.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>This specific web address is like a map pointer, telling the plugin exactly where to find the right reviews for your product.</p>



<p>You can now return to your WordPress dashboard, paste the URL into the &#8216;Page URL&#8217; field, and then click &#8216;Finish&#8217;.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="281" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg-url.png" alt="Entering the plugins' URL into the Page URL field" class="wp-image-368760" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg-url.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-addresources-wordpressorg-url-300x124.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>


<div class="wpb-alert style-blue">

<p><strong>üßë‚Äçüíª</strong> <strong>Pro Tip: </strong>The process works exactly the same whether you&#8217;re displaying plugin or theme reviews. Just make sure you&#8217;re copying the URL from the correct WordPress.org page.</p>

</div>


<p>Once connected, Reviews Feed Pro will automatically sync with WordPress.org to pull in the latest reviews for your chosen plugin or theme.</p>



<p>This ensures your displayed reviews stay current without any manual updates needed.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="331" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-wordpressorg-asresource.png" alt="WordPress.org link added" class="wp-image-368762" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-wordpressorg-asresource.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-addnew-wordpressorg-asresource-300x146.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>From here, just click &#8216;Next&#8217; to start customizing your reviews feed.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-4-customize-your-reviews-feed">Step 4: Customize Your Reviews Feed</h4>



<p>Reviews Feed Pro automatically generates a feed that matches your website&#8217;s existing design, but you can customize it to fit your needs.</p>



<p>You can start by selecting from the available pre-built templates. These templates provide different layouts and styling options that work well with most <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-wordpress-themes/" title="Most Popular and Best WordPress Themes (Expert Pick)">WordPress themes</a>.</p>



<p>After that, click &#8216;Next&#8217; to continue.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="436" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-review-template.png" alt="Choosing WordPress.org reviews feed template" class="wp-image-368764" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-review-template.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-review-template-300x192.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>On the next screen, you&#8217;ll see the visual customizer, where you can adjust your feed&#8217;s appearance.</p>



<p>Here, you can modify the header section, button styles, and individual review elements like <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-star-rating-plugins-for-wordpress/" title="Best Star Rating Plugins for WordPress (Compared)">star ratings</a> and user avatars. Every change you make appears instantly in the live preview panel on the right side of your screen.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="309" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-editor.png" alt="Reviews Feed Pro editor for WordPress org reviews" class="wp-image-369715" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-editor.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-editor-300x136.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>For example, if you go to the &#8216;Layout&#8217; section, you can choose between 3 main layout styles:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>List</strong> ‚Äì Reviews stacked vertically</li>



<li><strong>Masonry</strong> ‚Äì Pinterest-style grid</li>



<li><strong>Carousel</strong> ‚Äì Sliding reviews</li>
</ul>



<p>Don&#8217;t worry if you&#8217;re not sure which one to choose, because you can see how it looks in the preview.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="368" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-layout-list.png" alt="WordPress org reviews layout" class="wp-image-369717" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-layout-list.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-layout-list-300x162.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Next, one of my favorite features is the filtering system in the &#8216;Settings&#8217; tab.</p>



<p>It lets you filter reviews by star rating to show only 4-5 star reviews, or use keyword filtering to display reviews that mention specific terms. There&#8217;s even a banned words filter to exclude reviews containing specific phrases.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="388" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-filters.png" alt="Reviews Feed's filtering options" class="wp-image-369720" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-filters.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-filters-300x171.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>For complete control, you can manually moderate which reviews appear on your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/" title="How to Make a WordPress Website (Ultimate Guide)">WordPress site</a>.</p>



<p>This is especially helpful if you want to curate the most relevant and helpful reviews for your audience. For instance, you can use it to highlight reviews that discuss a specific feature you want to promote or mention your excellent customer support.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="369" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-moderation.png" alt="Enabling reviews moderation in Reviews Feed Pro" class="wp-image-369722" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-moderation.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeedpro-wordpressorg-editor-moderation-300x163.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-step-5-display-the-reviews-on-your-website">Step 5: Display the Reviews on Your Website</h4>



<p>When you&#8217;re satisfied with your feed&#8217;s appearance, click the &#8216;Embed&#8217; button in the top-right corner of the customizer. </p>



<p>This opens your embedding options.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="313" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embedbutton.png" alt="The Embed button in Reviews Feed Pro" class="wp-image-369726" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embedbutton.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embedbutton-300x138.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>You have three ways to display your reviews:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Add to a Page</strong>¬†lets you embed reviews directly into any existing <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/what-is-the-difference-between-posts-vs-pages-in-wordpress/" title="What Is the Difference Between Posts vs. Pages in WordPress?">post or page</a>. This is perfect for product pages or detailed plugin reviews.</li>



<li><strong>Add to a Widget</strong>&nbsp;allows you to show reviews in your sidebar, footer, or any other widget area. This works well for <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-rotating-testimonials-in-wordpress/" title="How to Add Rotating Testimonials in WordPress">displaying testimonials</a> site-wide.</li>



<li><strong>Copy Shortcode</strong>&nbsp;gives you a <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-a-shortcode-in-wordpress/" title="How to Add a Shortcode in WordPress (Beginner‚Äôs Guide)">shortcode</a> that you can paste anywhere on your site. This option provides the most flexibility for custom placements.</li>
</ul>



<p>For this example, let&#8217;s add reviews to a page ‚Äì choose &#8216;Add to a Page.&#8217;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="393" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-embedfeed-page.png" alt="Choosing the Add to a Page option on the Embed Feed popup" class="wp-image-368778" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-embedfeed-page.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-wordpressorg-embedfeed-page-300x173.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Then, you&#8217;ll select the page where you want the reviews to appear</p>



<p>Your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-themes/how-to-create-a-custom-homepage-in-wordpress/" title="How to Create a Custom Home Page in WordPress">home page</a> is a good start. It can use a simple list of positive reviews to create a strong first impression of trust and reliability.</p>



<p>So, let&#8217;s select the home page from the list and click the &#8216;Add&#8217; button.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="421" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embed-addtohome.png" alt="Adding reviews to the home page" class="wp-image-369728" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embed-addtohome.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/reviewsfeededitor-editor-embed-addtohome-300x186.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Next, in the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/14-tips-for-mastering-the-wordpress-visual-editor/" title="Tips for Mastering the WordPress Content Editor">content editor</a>, you can click the &#8216;+&#8217; button to add the Reviews Feed block.</p>



<p>Go ahead and use the search bar to quickly find the block.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="409" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed.png" alt="Adding Reviews Feed block" class="wp-image-369730" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed-300x180.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>Once you add the Reviews Feed block, you&#8217;ll immediately see the preview in the editor.</p>



<p>From here, you can move around this block to any position on your page using the standard <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-use-the-new-wordpress-block-editor/" title="How to Use the WordPress Block Editor (Gutenberg Tutorial)">WordPress block editor</a> controls.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="427" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed-loaded.png" alt="Reviews Feed added to the content editor" class="wp-image-369731" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed-loaded.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/blockeditor-add-reviewsfeed-loaded-300x188.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<p>When you&#8217;re happy with everything, hit &#8216;Save&#8217; or &#8216;Update&#8217; to publish your page.</p>



<p>Your WordPress.org reviews are now live and will automatically update as new reviews are posted to the original plugin or theme page.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="680" height="435" src="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/livesite-reviewsfeed-wordpressorg.png" alt="WordPres org reviews on a live site" class="wp-image-369735" srcset="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/livesite-reviewsfeed-wordpressorg.png 680w, https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/livesite-reviewsfeed-wordpressorg-300x192.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-bonus-step-maximize-conversions-by-featuring-reviews-on-key-pages">How to Maximize Conversions From WordPress.org Reviews</h4>



<p>Displaying your WordPress.org reviews in the <strong>right place</strong> can make a big difference in how many people install or buy your plugin or theme.</p>



<p>Here are some of the best places you can add your WordPress.org plugin or theme reviews:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>üí∞ <strong>Sales and product pages:</strong> Placing glowing reviews right next to your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-add-a-buy-now-button-in-wordpress/" title="How to Add a Buy Now Button in WordPress (Easy Methods)">&#8216;Buy Now&#8217; button</a> can be the final nudge a potential customer needs. It helps justify the price by showing that other happy customers have already chosen your product. </li>



<li>üß© <strong><a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-create-a-landing-page-with-wordpress/" title="How to Create a Landing Page With WordPress">Landing pages</a>:</strong> When someone visits a page about a specific plugin or theme, showing reviews right away builds instant trust and helps turn interest into action.</li>



<li>üõí <strong>Checkout pages:</strong> Even a small reviews widget with 4‚Äì5 star reviews can calm last-minute doubts and reduce cart abandonment.</li>
</ul>



<p>I‚Äôve found that pages with well-placed reviews convert better. The key is to show the right reviews on the right pages, based on what your visitors are looking for and <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-make-a-high-converting-sales-funnel-in-wordpress/" title="How to Make a High Converting Sales Funnel in WordPress">where they are in the buying process</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="aioseo-frequently-asked-questions-about-showing-wordpress-org-reviews">Frequently Asked Questions About Showing WordPress.org Reviews</h4>



<p>Here are a few questions that readers often ask me about showing WordPress.org reviews on their websites. </p>



<p><strong>How do I ensure WordPress.org reviews are updated automatically?</strong></p>



<p><a href="https://smashballoon.com/reviews-feed" target="_blank" title="Smash Balloon Reviews Feed - #1 Customer Reviews Plugin for WordPress">Reviews Feed Pro</a> automatically synchronizes with WordPress.org to pull in new reviews as they&#8217;re posted. The plugin checks for updates on a regular schedule, so your displayed reviews stay current without you needing to do anything. </p>



<p><strong>Can I customize which WordPress.org reviews are shown?</strong></p>



<p>Yes, you can filter reviews using several different methods within the Smash Balloon plugin. You can display only reviews above a certain star rating, filter by specific keywords that appear in review text, or use the banned words feature to exclude reviews containing unwanted terms.</p>



<p><strong>What should I do if I run into an authorization error with Smash Balloon?</strong></p>



<p>Authorization errors typically occur when the WordPress.org URL isn&#8217;t properly formatted or the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-fix-the-504-gateway-timeout-error-in-wordpress/" title="How to Fix the 504 Gateway Timeout Error in WordPress">connection has timed out</a>.</p>



<p>To fix this, you&#8217;ll want to double-check that you&#8217;ve copied the <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/website-url-parts-explained-for-beginners/" title="What Is a Website URL (Important Parts Explained for Beginners)">complete URL</a> from the plugin or theme&#8217;s WordPress.org page. Then, try reconnecting through the Smash Balloon Reviews Feed settings.</p>



<p><strong>Are there limits to the number of reviews I can display with Smash Balloon?</strong></p>



<p>The plugin doesn&#8217;t put strict limits on review numbers, but displaying too many reviews on a single page can slow down your site&#8217;s loading speed. I recommend <strong>starting with 5-10</strong> reviews per feed and testing your <a href="https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-performance-speed/" title="The Ultimate Guide to Boost WordPress Speed &amp; Performance">page performance</a> before adding more.</p>



